[
  {
    "text": "We've all seen movies",
    "start": 6.327,
    "duration": 1.157
  },
  {
    "text": "about terrible insects from outer space",
    "start": 7.484,
    "duration": 2.245
  },
  {
    "text": "or stories of abduction by little green men,",
    "start": 9.729,
    "duration": 2.565
  },
  {
    "text": "but the study of life in the universe,",
    "start": 12.294,
    "duration": 2.031
  },
  {
    "text": "including the possibility of extraterrestrial life,",
    "start": 14.325,
    "duration": 2.67
  },
  {
    "text": "is also a serious, scientific pursuit.",
    "start": 16.995,
    "duration": 3.092
  },
  {
    "text": "Astrobiology draws on diverse fields,",
    "start": 20.087,
    "duration": 3.18
  },
  {
    "text": "such as physics,",
    "start": 23.267,
    "duration": 0.893
  },
  {
    "text": "biology,",
    "start": 24.16,
    "duration": 1.025
  },
  {
    "text": "astronomy,",
    "start": 25.185,
    "duration": 0.985
  },
  {
    "text": "and geology,",
    "start": 26.17,
    "duration": 1.012
  },
  {
    "text": "to study how life was formed on Earth,",
    "start": 27.182,
    "duration": 2.169
  },
  {
    "text": "how it could form elsewhere,",
    "start": 29.351,
    "duration": 1.662
  },
  {
    "text": "and how we might detect it.",
    "start": 31.013,
    "duration": 1.882
  },
  {
    "text": "Many ancient religions described",
    "start": 33.495,
    "duration": 1.696
  },
  {
    "text": "other worlds inhabited by known human beings,",
    "start": 35.191,
    "duration": 2.914
  },
  {
    "text": "but these are more like mythical realms",
    "start": 38.105,
    "duration": 1.969
  },
  {
    "text": "or parallel universes",
    "start": 40.074,
    "duration": 1.443
  },
  {
    "text": "than other planets existing",
    "start": 41.517,
    "duration": 1.296
  },
  {
    "text": "in the same physical world.",
    "start": 42.813,
    "duration": 1.8
  },
  {
    "text": "It is only within the last century",
    "start": 44.613,
    "duration": 1.821
  },
  {
    "text": "that scientists have been able",
    "start": 46.434,
    "duration": 1.17
  },
  {
    "text": "to seriously undertake the search",
    "start": 47.604,
    "duration": 1.579
  },
  {
    "text": "for extraterrestrial life.",
    "start": 49.183,
    "duration": 2.201
  },
  {
    "text": "We know that at the most basic level",
    "start": 51.384,
    "duration": 1.912
  },
  {
    "text": "organisms on Earth need three things:",
    "start": 53.296,
    "duration": 2.156
  },
  {
    "text": "liquid water,",
    "start": 55.452,
    "duration": 0.893
  },
  {
    "text": "a source of energy,",
    "start": 56.345,
    "duration": 1.202
  },
  {
    "text": "and organic, carbon-based material.",
    "start": 57.547,
    "duration": 2.458
  },
  {
    "text": "We also know that the Earth",
    "start": 60.005,
    "duration": 1.371
  },
  {
    "text": "is just the right distance from the Sun,",
    "start": 61.376,
    "duration": 1.96
  },
  {
    "text": "so as not to be either frozen or molten.",
    "start": 63.336,
    "duration": 2.928
  },
  {
    "text": "So, planets within such a habitable range",
    "start": 66.264,
    "duration": 2.125
  },
  {
    "text": "from their own stars",
    "start": 68.389,
    "duration": 1.254
  },
  {
    "text": "may be able to support life.",
    "start": 69.643,
    "duration": 2.237
  },
  {
    "text": "But while we used to think",
    "start": 73.187,
    "duration": 1.162
  },
  {
    "text": "that life could only exist",
    "start": 74.349,
    "duration": 1.172
  },
  {
    "text": "in such Earth-like environments,",
    "start": 75.521,
    "duration": 1.881
  },
  {
    "text": "one of the most amazing discoveries of astrobiology",
    "start": 77.402,
    "duration": 2.722
  },
  {
    "text": "has been just how versatile life is.",
    "start": 80.124,
    "duration": 2.402
  },
  {
    "text": "We now know that life can thrive",
    "start": 82.526,
    "duration": 1.9
  },
  {
    "text": "in some of the most extreme environments",
    "start": 84.426,
    "duration": 1.821
  },
  {
    "text": "that'd be fatal for most known organisms.",
    "start": 86.247,
    "duration": 2.36
  },
  {
    "text": "Life is found everywhere,",
    "start": 88.607,
    "duration": 1.812
  },
  {
    "text": "from black smoke of hydrothermal vents",
    "start": 90.419,
    "duration": 2.132
  },
  {
    "text": "in the dark depths of Earth's oceans,",
    "start": 92.551,
    "duration": 2.054
  },
  {
    "text": "to bubbling, hot, acidic springs",
    "start": 94.605,
    "duration": 1.997
  },
  {
    "text": "on the flanks of volcanoes,",
    "start": 96.602,
    "duration": 1.671
  },
  {
    "text": "to high up in the atmosphere.",
    "start": 98.273,
    "duration": 2.381
  },
  {
    "text": "Organisms that live in these challenging environments",
    "start": 100.654,
    "duration": 2.48
  },
  {
    "text": "are called extremophiles,",
    "start": 103.134,
    "duration": 2.05
  },
  {
    "text": "and they can survive at extremes",
    "start": 105.184,
    "duration": 1.607
  },
  {
    "text": "of temperature,",
    "start": 106.791,
    "duration": 0.845
  },
  {
    "text": "pressure,",
    "start": 107.636,
    "duration": 0.801
  },
  {
    "text": "and radiation,",
    "start": 108.437,
    "duration": 0.997
  },
  {
    "text": "as well as salinity,",
    "start": 109.434,
    "duration": 1.036
  },
  {
    "text": "acidity,",
    "start": 110.47,
    "duration": 0.916
  },
  {
    "text": "and limited availability of sunlight,",
    "start": 111.386,
    "duration": 2.243
  },
  {
    "text": "water,",
    "start": 113.629,
    "duration": 0.869
  },
  {
    "text": "or oxygen.",
    "start": 114.498,
    "duration": 1.383
  },
  {
    "text": "What is most remarkable about these extremophiles",
    "start": 116.988,
    "duration": 2.357
  },
  {
    "text": "is that they are found thriving in environments",
    "start": 119.345,
    "duration": 2.054
  },
  {
    "text": "that mimic those on alien worlds.",
    "start": 121.399,
    "duration": 2.298
  },
  {
    "text": "One of the most important of these worlds",
    "start": 123.697,
    "duration": 2.211
  },
  {
    "text": "is our red and dusty neighbor, Mars.",
    "start": 125.908,
    "duration": 2.773
  },
  {
    "text": "Today, astrobiologists are exploring places",
    "start": 128.681,
    "duration": 3.055
  },
  {
    "text": "where life might once have existed on Mars",
    "start": 131.736,
    "duration": 2.492
  },
  {
    "text": "using NASA's Curiosity rover.",
    "start": 134.228,
    "duration": 2.306
  },
  {
    "text": "One of these is Gale Crater,",
    "start": 136.534,
    "duration": 1.799
  },
  {
    "text": "an impact crater created",
    "start": 138.333,
    "duration": 1.729
  },
  {
    "text": "when a meteor hit the surface of Mars",
    "start": 140.062,
    "duration": 1.527
  },
  {
    "text": "nearly 3.8 billions years ago.",
    "start": 141.589,
    "duration": 2.682
  },
  {
    "text": "Evidence from orbit suggest past traces of water,",
    "start": 144.271,
    "duration": 3.4
  },
  {
    "text": "which means the crater",
    "start": 147.671,
    "duration": 1.092
  },
  {
    "text": "might once have supported life.",
    "start": 148.763,
    "duration": 2.422
  },
  {
    "text": "Planets are not the only places",
    "start": 151.185,
    "duration": 1.656
  },
  {
    "text": "astrobiologists are looking at.",
    "start": 152.841,
    "duration": 2.087
  },
  {
    "text": "For example, Europa, one of the moons of Jupiter,",
    "start": 154.928,
    "duration": 2.59
  },
  {
    "text": "and Enceladus and Titan,",
    "start": 157.518,
    "duration": 1.682
  },
  {
    "text": "two of Saturn's moons,",
    "start": 159.2,
    "duration": 1.149
  },
  {
    "text": "are all exciting possibilities.",
    "start": 160.349,
    "duration": 2.246
  },
  {
    "text": "Although these moons are extremely cold",
    "start": 162.595,
    "duration": 2.423
  },
  {
    "text": "and two are covered in thick ice,",
    "start": 165.018,
    "duration": 1.829
  },
  {
    "text": "there is evidence of liquid oceans beneath the shell.",
    "start": 166.847,
    "duration": 3.181
  },
  {
    "text": "Could life be floating around in these oceans,",
    "start": 170.028,
    "duration": 2.922
  },
  {
    "text": "or could it be living around black smoker",
    "start": 172.95,
    "duration": 1.929
  },
  {
    "text": "vents at the bottom?",
    "start": 174.879,
    "duration": 1.959
  },
  {
    "text": "Titan is particularly promising",
    "start": 177.499,
    "duration": 1.822
  },
  {
    "text": "as it has an atmosphere",
    "start": 179.321,
    "duration": 1.144
  },
  {
    "text": "and Earth-like lakes, seas, and rivers",
    "start": 180.465,
    "duration": 2.28
  },
  {
    "text": "flowing across the surface.",
    "start": 182.745,
    "duration": 1.751
  },
  {
    "text": "It is very cold, however,",
    "start": 184.496,
    "duration": 1.433
  },
  {
    "text": "too cold for liquid water,",
    "start": 185.929,
    "duration": 1.616
  },
  {
    "text": "so these rivers may instead be flowing",
    "start": 187.545,
    "duration": 1.837
  },
  {
    "text": "with liquid hydrocarbons",
    "start": 189.382,
    "duration": 1.275
  },
  {
    "text": "such as methane and ethane.",
    "start": 190.657,
    "duration": 2.296
  },
  {
    "text": "These are composed of hydrogen,",
    "start": 192.953,
    "duration": 1.962
  },
  {
    "text": "and, more importantly, carbon,",
    "start": 194.915,
    "duration": 2.028
  },
  {
    "text": "which is the basic building block",
    "start": 196.943,
    "duration": 1.537
  },
  {
    "text": "of all life as we know it.",
    "start": 198.48,
    "duration": 1.775
  },
  {
    "text": "So, could life be found in these lakes?",
    "start": 200.255,
    "duration": 2.714
  },
  {
    "text": "Although instruments are being designed",
    "start": 202.969,
    "duration": 1.873
  },
  {
    "text": "to study these distant worlds,",
    "start": 204.842,
    "duration": 1.671
  },
  {
    "text": "it takes many years to build them",
    "start": 206.513,
    "duration": 1.834
  },
  {
    "text": "and even longer to get them",
    "start": 208.347,
    "duration": 1.19
  },
  {
    "text": "where they need to be.",
    "start": 209.537,
    "duration": 1.597
  },
  {
    "text": "In the meantime, astrobiologists work",
    "start": 211.134,
    "duration": 2.054
  },
  {
    "text": "in our own natural laboratory, the Earth,",
    "start": 213.188,
    "duration": 2.661
  },
  {
    "text": "to learn about all the weird",
    "start": 215.849,
    "duration": 1.259
  },
  {
    "text": "and wonderful forms of life that can exist",
    "start": 217.108,
    "duration": 2.271
  },
  {
    "text": "and to help us one day answer",
    "start": 219.379,
    "duration": 1.453
  },
  {
    "text": "one of humanity's oldest questions:",
    "start": 220.832,
    "duration": 2.233
  },
  {
    "text": "Are we alone?",
    "start": 223.065,
    "duration": 1.549
  }
]